    {
      "id": 231006,
      "category": "researcher",
      "content": "At the time of this report, Akismet API keys used formed part of the subdomain request to Akismetâ€™s backend in the form `api-key.rest.akismet.com`. This means that the API key is transmitted over DNS - a protocol that is [well known for its lack of encryption](https://developers.cloudflare.com/1.1.1.1/encryption/). \n\nAs a result, Akismet API keys cannot be considered secure or private. Anyone capturing network packets, or the DNS server operator for example, could easily log the DNS requests - and therefore API key - from a client accessing the Akismet API.\n\nThe unwanted disclosure of the API key could cause Denial of Service or Information Leakage should a malicious actor get hold of it.",
